social_posts.post_text:
I mean, who doesn’t love a good powder room? “The Bu” project (short for Malibu. Ha!) was all about creating a simple and serene space that didn’t lack statements. You can find the tiled powder room on page 169 in The Ultimate Bath Book. Thank you, @rizzolibooks! 

Photo by @douglasfriedman

This is your sign to not sacrifice comfort for design…

Some may think that in order to have a beautiful space there will be compromises made in terms of functionality and comfortability. The drama! I know that having a warm and cozy space will make me feel happy in a room which is a primary focus of mine if I am going to be spending a lot of time in it. 

What do you prioritize in your spaces? 

Photo by @douglasfriedman
I guess you could say so…

Me and my girl sitting pretty for the @robbreport. You can read all about my journey into the design world, my affinity for vintage pieces, and some routines I cherish.

Photo by @adamamengual

2022 core memories…
The Montecito Estate for @gwynethpaltrow will forever be a journey I cherish. Sharing this project with the world has further opened my eyes to the amazing community of design. I wouldn’t have chosen to do it with anyone else, GP.

Outdoor serenity. When styling outdoor spaces, I always want to ensure that I am complementing the elements we’re designing within. Is there history behind the location? What colors can I use to create balance? I believe your design should work with nature, not against it.

When designing the restrooms at the Allbright Club, I knew I wanted to make a statement. When going into any establishment, I always pay a little extra attention to the bathroom. I created an entirely submersive experience with floor to ceiling tiles creating a time capsule like space. 

Photos by @amandademme
It’s me and my shadow… 🤣

Although designing spaces is an art form in itself, there are some rules you can follow that will help you elevate your space. Here are some that I like to refer to when creating environments for my clients.

Holiday Cards are so special to me. They represent tradition, connection and are a special way to showcase seasons of life. This year I went to @minted for my holiday card. They have beautiful designer options from over 16,000 artists, are completely customizable and are so easy to order. Head to the link in my stories to check out their selection of holiday cards including the one I chose. #mintedpartner

What says Christmas more than a holiday mantel? I loved designing this vignette utilizing garland, stockings, wooden homes, and candelabras from artisan makers. This holiday season, @minted expanded its support of small businesses and artisans, creating a globally sourced catalog of home decor and original art that has been hand selected by experts for people like me who like to tap into their creativity during this time of year. Head to my stories to watch me style this mantel from start to finish. #mintedpartner

As Romanek Design Studios pauses for the holidays, I can’t help but reflect on what an incredible year it has been for us. We’ve poured our hearts and souls into every project that has been completed and continue to innovate for our active projects. Romanek Design Studios started from simply being passionate about creating environments in my own home and has expanded into something that I couldn’t even imagine. I have a feeling that 2023 is going to be an incredible year. 

Photo By @leannecantelon

One of my favorite ways to highlight the dramatic curve of a staircase is to utilize an entryway table with wild greenery on top of it. It brings the right amount of chaos, while feeling anchored when being viewed. 

Photo By @douglasfriedman
Some special projects that I got the honor of curating in the Los Angeles area. Have you been to any of these places? Tell me your favorite ones in the comments below!

I don’t go crazy over trends. I want the spaces I curate to be livable and luxe and eclectic and cool; somewhere you can see yourself spending a lifetime in. This typically can be represented with picking pieces from different eras that contrast in a nice way, but can also be seen utilizing complimentary colors in order to create balance. What are some of your favorite design eras to grab inspiration from? 

Photo by @douglasfriedman

Happy New Year! Ready for another incredible year with Romanek Design Studios. 

Photo by @adamamengual

If there’s one thing about me… I’ll take advantage of a dramatic art moment!

Photo by @douglasfriedman
I love collecting books. It’s an amazing way to style surfaces while showcasing interests, history, and design. Here are some of my recent favorites that I’ve utilized on some tabletops!

A small kitchen can be equally as impactful as a grandiose one. The goal? To make it a space that will one day tell stories of people gathering together. 

Photo by @douglasfriedman
On set with my girl.

I love these steel doors that give a 360 view of my client’s den. It makes what was once a small, closed off space feel wide and open. 

Photo by @douglasfriedman

Another look at my kitchen design at the Isle project. I love choosing colors that morph with the light that seeps through the windows. In daylight, the subtle color really shines but at night it transforms into a more neutral color. 

Paired with this incredible range from @monogramappliances and we have a perfect match. 

Photo by @leannecantelon

Laurel Canyon is such a special place filled with deep musical history. Bringing this to life in my Laurel Canyon home was invigorating. From the Los Angeles light seeping through the windows, to the aged molding that frames the doorways, there is so much to be discovered with every corner.
Thank you, @robbreport, for chatting with me about cars, fashion, and of course, design. You can read the article at the link in bio.

My client had an unbelievable art collection that I needed to put to work! When it comes to extremely unique pieces that are bold and almost whisper stories to you while viewing it, I want the space to be equally as interesting. This historic West Hollywood home was truly a match made from above with wooden ceilings, french doors, and stone floors that balanced the gallery that was about to fill it. 

Photo by @douglasfriedman

I am so thrilled to announce the launch of @tonic_xyz, a platform that will empower a whole new generation of collectors and artists. As someone who loves to collect one of a kind pieces, being a founding partner for Tonic has been so incredible, and I can’t wait to share it with you all. 

Join me and Tonic on January 26 @ 4:30PM PT for a conversation about what we’re building! We’ve got some surprise guests and even a gift for you! You can RSVP at tonic.xyz. It’s going to be special.
Thank you, @manzilibyhuda, for this incredible piece of art!!! I’m absolutely in love with it. Now, where to hang it?

I really love how @thisisthegreat_ at Sportsmen’s Lodge came together. We kept it minimal and moody to allow certain design elements to shine. (Can we take a moment for the chandelier??) Love you girls so much!!!

Woke up this Tuesday feeling EXCITED because @theexpert just officially launched their e-commerce platform, Showroom!! I always point those who ask about where I source paint colors, artwork, and furniture to The Expert because it’s truly a one stop shop for all things interior design led by some of the best of the best in the industry. Today, you can shop my very own Showroom which includes over 100 of my favorite pieces by some of my go-to vendors like @nickeykehoe @apparatus @lawsonfenning @schumacher and @nordicknots.

Head to the link in my bio to shop my Showroom.
Someone get this girl on payroll! Loving the LA chair from my collaboration with @mgbwhome extra recently.

Thank you, @curateur, for featuring me on the cover of the latest edition of CURATEUR Magazine! Always love chatting with my sis @rachelzoe. We talked about my favorite elements of my home, personal style, and design during the holidays. 

You can read the latest edition of CURATEUR and shop my edit at the link in bio. Use code BRIGETTE25 to get 25% off your first purchase.

Hey @mollybsims, do you have space for me in your Hamptons home? 🤣 I keep coming back to this project because I love how it really represents Molly’s personal style. It’s eclectic and fun with practicality in mind so she can create a laid back atmosphere for her family and friends.

My favorite Sunday mornings include all the things I love, waking up early to read, walks around the neighborhood with my daughters, listening to music, and cuddling the pups!! The new Lazy Sunday Morning diffuser from @maisonmargielafragrances smells like those beautiful Sunday mornings #MargielaHomePartner #SmellsLikeMemories
January compositions. It’s all about how and where you place things.
Exploring some new pieces and fell in love with the gorgeous DJ Rosé coffee table by @bridge.and.fog
Roxy and Rufus are always making their way into the shot!! They love the limelight 🤣
Sneak peek into my favorite outdoor havens…daydreaming of summer now
An honor to be featured in @harpersbazaarus to share my love for my @hermes Constance Micro III handbag that I was lucky enough to inherit from my grandmother!!
Some more @petittroisla le Valley angles. Forever in love with these checkerboard floors 🖤🤍
One final moment for a project that is close to my heart – Isle. 🤍

Creating some interest with these contrasting chairs by @pierre_augustin_rose. The light that radiates through these french doors is unbeatable. 

Photo by @leannecantelon
There are so many little gems throughout this home!! Would love to hear what caught your eye in the comments 👀
There are so many little gems throughout this home!! Would love to hear what caught your eye in the comments 👀
@thefrankieshop is always a closet staple. Classic meets comfort.
In magic maker heaven!!! Frieze LA has left me feeling so inspired. Can’t wait to bring some of these fresh ideas to life!

Happy Black History Month. These African American artists works that I’m admiring are powerful, beautiful, and full of life. Thank you creators. Comment below if you’d like more information on these artists.

THESE WINDOWS in the game room create an immersive experience allowing my client to embrace the beautiful botany of Malibu.

Photo by @douglasfriedman

It's almost here!! I'm so excited that Tonic’s next collection "Intimità" by the insanely talented NFT artist @stefan_contiero will be released this Thursday at 10 AM. To learn more about the incredible Stefano collection and RSVP, head to @tonic_xyz

I grew up in a musical household, so when the opportunity arose to style this Gran Nichetto Limited Edition piano from @steinwayandsons designed by @lucanichetto, it was a no brainer! Done and done. 

This color that @nichettostudio created anchors this room perfectly. It’s a Midnight Red variation, crafted in hand-selected Macassar, with elegantly sculpted legs and brass accents. I can already envision people gathering around the piano. #ad
Keeping the hands (and energy!) of Isle clean in this moody powder room.
Hey there, @delilah 🤍 Loved bringing this Las Vegas classic to life in West Hollywood!
When designing the spaces at Lifehood, we wanted each room to totally envelope the visitors. These draped ceilings pull you into the space and invite you to cozy up on these chairs.
Thank you @lovehappensmag for featuring me in the most recent issue of the Tempted by Design series, for my project with @gwynethpaltrow, whom I love and adore!
Last night with @goop 🤍 There’s nothing like an atmosphere of powerful women supporting one another. Well done @gwynethpaltrow, you did a beautiful job.
Finishing touches with @colinking.

Life’s been busy, but I am extremely grateful for it all.  Swipe for some of my favorite moments recently. 

〰️ @friezeofficial inspires me each year

〰️ Spoke on a panel with the most amazing designers; @sarahellisonstudio, @gabbois and @argyledesign.co hosted by the magical @cozy.spice 

〰️ Celebrated my @martynbullard launching his new terrazzo collection with @annsacks (and I got to squeeze @nturnerdesign! What a treat.) 

〰️ Sourced some incredible vessels for clients at @oliveateliers 

〰️ Met with my girls @emilyandmeritt for some exciting new projects (keep an eye out at @thisisthegreat_)

When I got the first glimpse of my home, I knew preserving historical elements like the crown molding would be a priority of mine, using it as the framework that will tell the story of my design. Here are some of my favorite historical designs that make my heart flutter!

HONORED to be named as one of the Top Black Interior Designers Today by @housedigestofficial. I still can’t believe that I get to do what I love for a living. Thank you so much for supporting my journey.
Tile Trends. 〰️ Using different shapes,  textures and colors is an interesting way to switch up your walls; whether it be a powder room or a merchandise display, have fun with your design!

Thank you @1stdibs for including me in the Top 50 Designers. Means the world to me. Everyone knows that I love what I get to do everyday and this only makes it more amazing!! Thank you, thank you!!! #1stDibs50

Some recent color story play. 🥳 I love using this as an exercise to keep my creativity flowing. My eye has been drawn towards these 70s tones and textures recently. Which one do you want to see in your design?
Inspired by vintage Italian lighting, our @mgbwhome & @brigetteromanek collaborative collection will make any room in your home shine bright. ✨

A beautiful evening with @1stdibs celebrating their Top 50 Designers last weekend. I consider myself so lucky to be surrounded by so much creativity and talent. Thank you again. 🤍

Photos by: Madison McGaw/BFA.com
Adding greenery is a finishing touch that is guaranteed to breathe life into a space. Save this video for your next plant sourcing excursion and let me know what your favorites are 🌿
Join me at Romanek Design Studio. 🤍 My home away from home.
Thank you, @hermes for sending me and hosting me on one of the most incredible and inspiring trips of my design life.
THANK YOU @flauntmagazine for this incredibly generous feature. Your words brought me so much joy. Eternally grateful for what I get to do. 🤍
Tough day at the office.
While in Italy, @hermes curated the most inspiring trips to galleries and museums… Inspiration is overflowing.
Like a kid in a candy store.
THANK YOU @homesandgardensofficial 🤍 So blessed to have been included alongside so many incredible designers. Having lived in England, the UK will always feel like home to me.

April was a month I will never forget. Swipe to see some special highlights 👉🏽
• Visiting an original Gio Ponti restored apartment in Italy. I guess we both like pink! 
• Dinner with the @hermes team and some incredible designers. 
• Had the most incredible experience with @we.are.ona. 
• @barnaba_fornasetti is as stylish as his homeware. 
• @wsj dinner for @isaloniofficial. 
• Hangs with my brother @mishakahn in Milan.

I know organic shapes are all the rage, but the way it is paired with different elements in a space can create a classic design. I love how the curvature in the couch plays with the curves in the sconces.
LOVED being the surprise keynote alongside my brother @jakearnold at @design_camp_co. Connecting with the greater design community is something I will never take for granted. Thanks for having me!
Had an incredible time with @wsj Magazine celebrating Milan Design Week with some of the best in the industry. Thank you for having me!
Happy Mother’s Day @thepaulettemcwilliams 🤍 I love you forever.

THIRTEEN LUNE. 🤍
So proud of @nyakio for coming up with such a brilliant idea to create an inclusive skin/beauty care business. Thank you for making good and clean products available to everyone. Honored to play a part in creating this brick and mortar.
Behind the scenes on what an onsite design meeting looks like. Dreaming up the possibilities of what I can create with my clients is one of my favorite parts of this job.
Thinking back to sourcing for clients with @oliveateliers last month. Tip of the month: Mix old with new to add some soul.
@thisisthegreat_ on Abbot Kinney. Channeling all of the cabin vibes at this one. 🪵
I had such an inspiring time last week at @blueskyauberge surrounded by so many incredible women. I am eternally grateful. Nothing like sisterhood.
Passion > Everything. Passion for what you’re doing = creating something you’re proud of.

I am so excited to be designing the primary bathroom and closet in the second annual @livingbydesignshowhouse. Hint: I’m loving green lately. 🐊 I’ll be sharing some sneak peaks of the spaces I designed leading up to the launch in September, so stay tuned. #LivingByDesignShowhouse  Producer @embello_inc Visualization @yousee.studio Tile @annsacks Organization @caclosets Paint @dunnedwardsdura Plumbing @kohler Lighting @lampsplus Art & Decor @minted Outdoor Furnishings @summerclassics Flooring @tmbr_flooring
Discovering innovative ways to display merchandise is a puzzle! Where the opportunities are endless! What are some of your favorite ways to showcase items?
Let’s talk lighting. From the color of bulbs used to the style of fixture, the way a room is lit can completely transform the atmosphere.
Another collaboration with @emilyandmeritt for @thisisthegreat_. This never gets old!
SICK, SICK, SICK. This sofa by @sarahellisonstudio is EVERYTHING. I’m so proud of my girl and it’s SUPER comfy!

Good morning, Rodeo Drive! Designing the storefront for the iconic @piaget in Beverly Hills was such an amazing experience. I love getting to be a part of the journey for companies that hold history in their field.
How is 2023 already halfway through?!?! So grateful for what these first 6 months have held, but I have a feeling that the next few are going to be even better. 🤐
Think outside the box. I love this butcher block turned vanity at my Laurel Canyon home. Unexpected and harmonious. 🤍
Because everyone’s summer house in the Hamptons should be pure magic. A favorite of mine.
Roxy and Rufus celebrating their independence. 🐶 Happy Fourth!
Thank you for having me, @convoxdesign! Loved getting the opportunity to chat through all things design. You can listen to the entire episode now through the link in my bio.
Divine designs. 🤍🤍

If you’d have asked me, even a year ago, if I’d ever have a book, I would have said not a chance. But I did it.. and it’s almost here! And I can’t wait to share it with you all. 

Livable Luxe isn’t just a book title to me. It’s what I live by — The art of incredibly beautiful spaces that are meant to be lived in. Meant to enjoy. 

Thank you to the people who saw me, hired me, and trusted me to bring these projects to life. I am forever grateful. 

LIVABLE LUXE – 10.10.23
Available for pre order through the link in my bio 🤍
Sometimes all you need to do is add some chairs and let nature speak for itself.
Now playing at Romanek Design Studio 🎧
Who said design can’t be fun? I love when my clients want to play with color.
Through the eyes of my daughters…photos of me and my work. 🤍
When the vision starts to come to life…there’s no better feeling.

Thank you, @vogue, for chatting with me about Japandi. It was so fun to revisit my Hamptons project with @mollybsims and talk about the ease this design style can bring to our lives. Visit the link in my stories to read the full feature.
Some recent moments that make my heart happy.

Flipping through the pages of my book (I can’t believe I get to say that!!) has been so surreal. I am so proud of the work I have accomplished. I am so honored that I get to design for so many incredible people. What was once a hobby has turned into my world, and I wouldn’t exchange it for anything else. 

Pre order at the link in my bio. 🤍
All in a week’s work.
Weekend moodboard 🛋️
Melrose mirrored mayhem designed by yours truly.

Three reasons I love this vignette at Isle…

— The Crown Molding
— My lighting collaboration with @mgbwhome 
— This vintage Desede sofa. ✨

The perfect mix of old and new with a touch of Romanek flare.
@thisisthegreat_ at One Paseo 🌊 I love how we take the same elements and innovate the design each time. It stays true to the brand, but never feels old.

A lovely evening in Malibu with @bulgari 🖤

What an absolutely beautiful evening with beautiful women who do beautiful things. Dinner with a view, serpenti jewelry, luxurious leather handbags…what more can a girl ask for? 

Thank you to the Bulgari team for connecting me with these beautiful women who I am happy to know. Such an amazing experience.

Reflecting upon Livable luxe, I’ve learned that…

I love an orchid arrangement. 
I love texture. 
I love when materials contrast. 
I love playing with color. 
I love a mix of old and new. 
I love my job. 

Pre order Livable Luxe through the link in bio. 🤍
Working on something special with my girls. 🤍🤍🤍
Trust the process. Enjoy it. The final result is always worth it.

Monday night was a celebration of the opening of the @audemarspiguet private showroom. I was lucky enough to be the designer for the space and I’m in love with it. Thank you, AP house, for an incredible night, and incredible clientele, and incredible team!
A moment at my AP project.

This week, I spoke with the @nytimes while choosing a new color for my primary bedroom. There’s a multitude of shades and hues and companies to choose from. Making the decision that feels right for you can feel overwhelming! But when you nail it, and it's right, that little thing you did with that gallon of paint will completely change the space.

You can read all of my tips and tricks in this weekend's newspaper. Thank you @tmckeough and @michaeltyronedelaney for your wonderful words and images.

Thank you, @cultured_mag, for featuring Livable Luxe in this feature. Beyond blessed to see my book listed alongside so many incredible designers. October 10th can’t come quick enough! Pre order your copy now at the link in bio.

When the iconic watch brand approached me about designing their Los Angeles Showroom, I knew exactly what I wanted to bring to the space. Cali colors, cool spaces, and a sense of relaxed lux. Thank you to the wonderful @audemarspiguet team for this opportunity, and thank you @elledecor for the debut feature. A wonderful time had by all!

I was excited to be asked to be a part of the second annual @livingbydesignshowhouse. To design a dream bathroom with a bunch of amazing brands. A bathroom to exhale and relax in. An in home spa retreat. You can see a full tour through the link in my stories.

Malibu Love. 🤍

This is a perfect example of livable luxe. Every piece I installed is a beautiful, usable work of art.

Beautiful, functional, unique pieces, that you enjoy for years to come, is what “Livable Luxe” means to me. Rooms should be usable and enjoyable without sacrificing luxury. Enjoy your love letter to yourself, meaning your home. 💌

V.I.P. 

A private conversation area at @audemarspiguet’s latest showroom in Los Angeles.

I love interior design coffee table books. Really fun to peruse. In Livable Luxe, I wanted to share beautiful imagery, but I also wanted to share some of my journey and how I have gotten to make my passion my career. This is a question I’m asked about often! I share a few antidotes and I hope some inspiring messages. 🤍 Pre order now through the link in my bio.
Getting up close and personal at Malibu Love. 🌊

Chalet for The Day. ⛷️

In Livable Luxe, this chapter is called Chalet for The Day. It gives the feeling of being on a mountain top with a cozy environment, soft, vivid colors and beautiful textures.
I love these two people.
It’s all in the details.

We’re officially 3 days away from Livable Luxe’s publication date. My first book ever. 

If you would have asked me when I was a kid if I were to have written a book, I would have said, ‘Not a chance!!!’ But when you have a passion, a love, and something you just believe in wholeheartedly, you never know where it will lead to. Believe in yourself and keep walking forward. 🤍
Design has moments. These are some of my favorite at one of my recent installs in NYC. 🤍

I can’t believe it’s here. My publication date. When I was asked by a journalist a few years ago what my style was, the phrase ‘Livable Luxe’ just sprang to mind. That has always been my design ethos. 

Thank you to my mom, Missy, Willow, Isobel, Ari, Liat, Orly, Amir, Mark R, Gwyneth, Melissa, Gabriella, Nareg, Alix, Amy, Courtney, Madi, Kelly R, Kelly P, J&B, Gloria, Steve, Sara, Jen, Demi, Rebecca, Ethan, Michael, Jake,  Anna, Jessica, Blanca, Rachel, Amy, Mayer, Asad, Douglas, Estee, Kelly S, Emily, Merritt, Martyn, Nicole, and Kent. 

Clearly it takes a village. 🤍

Order ‘Livable Luxe’ now through the link in bio.

It’s been one week since the release of ‘Livable Luxe’. I’m blown away by all of the support from my friends, family, and everyone who has played a role in my journey as a designer. Tonight, we celebrated. Thank you, thank you, thank you. 🤍 @audemarspiguet #AudemarsPiguet

New York City, I'm excited to share ‘Livable Luxe’ with you. Join me and my friend @derekblasberg in conversation next week on Tuesday, October 24, from 6-7:30pm. Hosted by @rockefellercenter in partnership with @mcnallyjackson, the first 40 people to purchase the book online or in-store will receive a seat to the event. Visit the link in my stories for more details. See you soon!

Thank you so much to my clients, friends, family, and colleagues that came out during this challenging time to support me with my first book. The really wonderful thing is that the room was filled with love and kindness and warmth. I will be forever grateful. And a special thank you to my daughter Isobel for an incredible playlist. @audemarspiguet #AudemarsPiguet
The plan was for about 80 but over 200 came and showed love. It was everything to me. I’m soooooooooooo grateful. Thank you!
It’s all in the details. Thank you @audemarspiguet and @cocktail_acdmy for a beautiful evening.
Layer, layer, layer. Layering different materials and colors creates a warm, personal, dynamic design.

Last night was a night I won’t forget — In NYC, with my friend @derekblasberg, talking about the beautiful subject of design. 

I’ve said it before, I’m so grateful. Thank you, Derek. Thank you, @rockefellercenter. Thank you, @pebblebarnyc, for an incredible night.
There’s nothing like celebrating with the design community in the city. Thank you, thank you, thank you. Your support means the world to me!

Last night, I got to share a little bit about the journey of creating @audemarspiguet Los Angeles showroom. The chemistry between myself and @ginwright’s vision resulted in a magical, ‘California cool’ space. I’m in love!

Nights of inspiration with @audemarspiguet.🤍 So incredibly blessed to have been a part of these special nights with @goop, @elledecor and @vanityfair hosted at AP House. 

Seeing the showroom filled with amazing people makes my heart happy.
Perspective changes everything. #RomanekMoments
October 2023, you’re a month I’ll never forget.
In a simple, clean space, it needs to be all about the details.
The Blue Lagoon 💙 I love how this room has a monochromatic feel to it. Playing with different tones of the same color gives a rich, layered feel to the room. Obsessed!

At home with Livable Luxe. 

Seeing my book in the homes of so many, including my own, is so crazy. Thank you for all of your support! I’ll never forget this time in my life.
Golden hour ☁️ @loloirugs @amberinteriors

BTS of my feature in @vanityfair with @gigi.mcdowell in @audemarspiguet Los Angeles showroom. (Designed by me!) 🤳

You can read the full article on our ‘Mentorship That Was Meant To Be’ at the link in bio.
My tour of the brand new @crateandbarrel with @brauerseb. I’m so proud of my friends there!!

One of my favorite touches to add into a design is a beautiful orchid arrangement. If you’ve ever been to one of my projects, you’ll start to familiarize yourself with them. Orchids are delicate, exotic and elegant. They symbolize luxury, beauty and strength, and I just really love that.
Hoping you and yours had a wonderful Thanksgiving. I’m thankful to you all for supporting me and my work. And to my friends, family and clients. 🤍

Growing up, I was seeing so many different things, so many different styles, so many different environments and atmospheres. Wherever the new home would be, was my respite. That was my safe space.

And now, interior design has turned into my world. Thank you, @elleusa, for allowing me to open the doors of my 1929 home to you. You can read the full feature through the link in my bio.
A peek inside an interior designer's camera roll. 🎞️
Me and my shadow.
